  "name": "RPlog_The_Penance_of_Lynae_Cassius",
  "title": "The Whip That Struck Stone",
  "summary": "In the unfinished Spire of Reconciliation at the New Alderaan Jedi Temple, Master Luke Skywalker convenes a private tribunal over the war crimes of the former Imperial officer Dr. Lynae Cassius, who commanded the orbital bombardment of Cochran. Before assembled senators, military witnesses including the Chyleni pilot Kyrin Sh'vani and the marine Wrista, the stoic guard Sergeant Holden Deckherd, the senator Del, and a quietly devoted late arrival named Mahon, Luke challenges the gathering to consider whether any of them, raised under Imperial doctrine, would have walked a different path. Lynae refuses to grovel, defiantly owning her actions as a matter of honor and indicting both sides for the war's endless cycle of vengeance, then bares her scarred back and offers her flesh in penance. When Luke instead presses the whip upon the bloodthirsty senators, none will take it -- the Cochran representative declining outright -- and Luke ultimately cracks the whip against the stone floor, declaring Lynae forgiven. A brief Force-vision from Luke and a respectful bow from Kyrin follow, and the proceeding dissolves into a pointed exchange in which Del, refusing to hate Lynae, offers her office's help, and Lynae accepts the chance to forge a new life serving the CDU and Republic.",
